post_text:
Support WHS FCA Water Drive
Washington HS FCA is hosting a water drive for the elementary. If you would like to donate cases of water, that would be awesome! Our FCA students will be giving water to kids at school in the mornings who are not able to bring a water bottle to school, or forgot to bring water to school during the day. Due to COVID-19, our school is discouraging using the water fountains. Students have PE, recess, and just need to be hydrated throughout the day. So, if you’d like to donate, we would much appreciate it! You can drop it off at the HS office if you would like to help!
Thank you!

wps-isd.com/35229?articleID=58963

TOMORROW, (8/11) is the DAY!

Attention all Pre-K Parents:

Prekindergarten Parent Orientation
When:
Tuesday, Aug. 11th, 4pm
Where:
201 Kerby Avenue Washington, OK
More information
Parent only meeting in the cafeteria on August 11th. Orientation will be a time for parents to meet teachers and learn prekindergarten expectations. Please bring student school supplies to the meeting.

In addition, we would like to invite “Children ONLY” to a fun ”PreK practice school day hour” on Wednesday, August 12th, at the following times in your child’s new classroom.

9:00 a.m.-10:00 a.m.- Children whose last name begins with A-L.
1:00 p.m.- 2:00 p.m.- Children whose last name begins with M-Z.

Attention all Pre-K Parents:

Prekindergarten Parent Orientation
When:
Tuesday, Aug. 11th, 4pm
Where:
201 Kerby Avenue Washington, OK
More information
Parent only meeting in the cafeteria on August 11th. Orientation will be a time for parents to meet teachers and learn prekindergarten expectations. Please bring student school supplies to the meeting.

In addition, we would like to invite “Children ONLY” to a fun ”PreK practice school day hour” on Wednesday, August 12th, at the following times in your child’s new classroom.

9:00 a.m.-10:00 a.m.- Children whose last name begins with A-L.
1:00 p.m.- 2:00 p.m.- Children whose last name begins with M-Z.

post_text:
Starting today, you can pick up your student's enrollment packet outside their building. All students must fill out and turn in the packet. You can print the packet off online... however, there isn't an online option to submit information. Only a "new to district" student registration is offered online. If you submitted an online registration, you will still need to fill out a packet. Thank you, for your cooperation.

Back to School Packets are required for ALL WPS students. The packet will include important documents such as updated demographic information and proof of residency.

Thursday July 30th Packets will be available both on our website www.wps-isd.com and in a box outside the main doors of the elementary, middle school, and high school. Packets are to be returned to your student's main office on the 3rd of August from 12 pm - 7 pm or on the 4th of August from 7 am to 12 pm. Please complete and return all documents in the packet.

WHS Graduation Ceremony Scheduled for 6/20 Moved to Event Center
Updated 6-19-20

2020 GRADUATION CEREMONY DETAILS





DATE: 6/20/2020

TIME: 9:30 AM

Doors Open: 8:30 AM

Venue Change: Warrior Event Center



The 2020 Washington High Schools Graduation ceremony will be open to the community. We ask that every attempt be made to abide by social distancing guidelines.



Washington Public Schools recommends that all attendees follow the CDC guidelines.



CDC guidelines:https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/prevention.html



Ticket Seating:

Each graduate may select four family members to sit on the gym floor. (Tickets must be presented for court access)



Senior Citizen & Handicapped Seating:

We ask that the top floor seating inside the WEC be reserved for those who are disabled and our senior citizens.



General Seating: All seating will be open to guests. Where possible, please sit in family groups and allow for social distancing.

Oklahoma Promise Information for 10th Grade Parents Who Experienced a Recent Loss of Income
Oklahoma’s Promise: Alert for 10th-Grade Parents With Recent Income Loss

If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income.

The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline.

You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received.

Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu



Apply at: https://www.okhighered.org/okpromise/

Oklahoma Promise Information for 10th Grade Parents Who Experienced a Recent Loss of Income
Oklahoma’s Promise: Alert for 10th-Grade Parents With Recent Income Loss

If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income.

The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline.

You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received.

Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu



Apply at: https://www.okhighered.org/okpromise/

Summer EBT Program Available
The Chickasaw Nation is offering a Summer EBT for Children.Native and non-Native students enrolled in participating schools and receiving free and reduced school meals may qualify for free food this summer. Qualifying families will receive an EBT card (works like a debit card) that allows you to purchase healthy food for the summer.

To apply online or for more information ,go to Chickasaw.net/SummerEBT. To apply over the phone, call (580) 272-1178or (844) 256-3467 (8 a.m. to 5 p.m., Monday-Friday).

Application Deadline is August 3, 2020.

post_text:
Recently, Mrs. Hedenberg had her 6th grade students nominate a song (any song..current, Broadway, Disney, etc) that could relate to to the current situation going on with the world today and how much we truly need each other during all of this.
Students had to choose a song, explain why they chose it, how it made them feel to listen to, and how it applies to what is happening today.
They had asked all semester if Mrs. Hedenberg would sing in class and they never got the chance to.
Mrs. Hedenberg told them that whatever song WON, that she would sing the song and include it in a video.

The winner is: Sam Cantrell

Directions: Students pick one question to answer, take a picture of yourself for the yearbook, include your name and grade and send it to hollyminson@wps-isd.com
EX. What is something positive that you can take out of this situation?
I get to focus more on myself during this time. - Holly Minson (Senior)

THE QUESTIONS ARE:

1. How are you staying connected with your friends?

2. What is something positive that you can take out of this situation?

3. What is something that you do to pass time?

Thanks for participating!

Free WIFI Options Available for Washington Students During Distance Learning
Washington Public Schools and First Baptist Church Washington are offering free wi-fi options while students are distance learning. To use wifi at the school, pull up in the high school parking lot (as close to the commons windows as possible). Login in: wpsguest , no password needed. To use free wifi from the church parking lot, use log in: distancelearning. For the password, call the school, Monday- Thursday from 8-12 at 288-0158.

Senior Cap and Gown Pick Up
Washington High School seniors, with recent events unfolding in our state, and in an attempt to get our seniors their cap, gown, and announcements, Jostens will be offering a “drive-thru” delivery at their office. Their address is 14830 Bristol Park Blvd, Edmond, OK 73013. WHS has a date set up for Tuesday, April 7th from 10 am – 2 pm. If you still have a balance they ask that you go online to Jostens.com or call 1-800-JOSTENS/ 1-800-567-8367. They will not be accepting cash at the delivery for your safety and their staff’s safety.

To OUR 2020 Washington Warrior baseball team ! SENIORS: Thank you for your time and effort in leaving this program where it stands today , ON THE RISE ! Your willingness to be coached , disciplined and molded makes your coaches so proud ! UNDERCLASSMEN : Don’t take things for GRANTED !!!! This unprecedented time should reveal to you that you’re never given tomorrow ! Let’s all grow together for OUR next opportunity to compete again as a PROGRAM ! PARENTS : We as coaches want to THANK YOU for allowing us to help mold and make your sons into good baseball players , but even better MEN ! Your support of this program financially , emotionally and through your prayers will never go unnoticed ! COACH K -Coach Lucas -Coach Johnson -Coach Haggard

WPS is commited to making sure all of our students are fed during the state mandated shutdown. Together, we will get through this.

Free Meals Provided For Enrolled WPS Students During Shutdown
Free “Grab and Go” meals will be provided for students enrolled in Washington Public Schools during the state mandated shut down. Meals will be available for pick up between Monday-Friday from 9:30 a.m.- 11:00 a.m. Students will receive a breakfast and lunch entree during pickup.

Pick up meals on the west side of the cafeteria. Vehicles enter the west side of the elementary off of Kirby Street. Meals will be handed through the driver’s car window and vehicles will exit to the south by the bus barn/ Mcalister Gym on to Turner street.

For delivery, call 288-6190

post_text:
Washington FFA Bonus Auction
Washinton FFA Bonus Auction is in full swing. The local show was held on February 22nd , with the bonus auction on Tuesday, February 25th . Everyone is invited to attend the free BBQ dinner from 5-7p.m. The auction will start at 7:00 p.m. Anyone in the community can make a tax exempt donation to the bonus auction.

The Washington Bonus Auction has been a wonderful community tradition for the past 20 years. The auction is an opportunity for local sponsors to support several young people whose livestock projects have been selected as superior. The Bonus Auction will work much as other auctions, except that ownership of the animal project does not change hands. The successful bidders are providing a bonus or premium to the exhibitors who have excelled in the managment and presentation of their livestock project. Thank you to everyone who has supported these students!
